msContents.summary: A volume of the ḥadīth collection of al-Bukhārī; contains from the beginning of "Kāf-hā-yā-ʻayn-ṣād" through the end of "Kitāb al-aḍāḥī"; some marginalia.

supportDesc.extent: 193 leaves : 271 x 198 (168 x 107) mm, bound to 272 x 206 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in maghribī in dark brown ink; pointed, partially vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated chapter title frame for the first chapter in gold, blue, and red in a mosaic pattern with illuminated roundel in the margin (f. 1v); slightly smaller marginal roundel in the same colors at end (f. 176r). Rubrications in red, blue and gold.

binding.p: Bound in red leather with flap; blind stamped central toronja and corner pieces; coordinating blind stamped mandorla on flap; blind ruled frame.
